# MCP Credentials — Sample Template
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ------------------
# 1. Copy this file to your home directory:
#        cp .mcp-credentials.sample ~/.mcp-credentials
# 2. Set permissions so only you can read it:
#        chmod 600 ~/.mcp-credentials
# 3. Fill in your real values below (replace the placeholder strings)
# 4. Source it from your shell profile (~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc):
#        [ -f ~/.mcp-credentials ] && source ~/.mcp-credentials
# 5. Restart your terminal, then restart Claude Code.
#
# SECURITY RULES
# --------------
# - NEVER commit this file (it is in .gitignore — the .sample version is safe)
# - NEVER paste a real key into .claude/settings.*.json — only ${VAR} placeholders go there
# - Rotate any key immediately if it is ever accidentally exposed
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Google / Stitch (AI UI generation — stitch.withgoogle.com) ───────────────
# Get your key: Stitch Settings page → API Keys → Create API Key
export STITCH_API_KEY="your-stitch-api-key-here"

# ── GitHub MCP (repo/issue/PR access) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your token: github.com → Settings → Developer Settings → Personal Access Tokens
# export GITHUB_TOKEN=""

# ── Linear MCP (issue tracking) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your key: linear.app → Settings → API → Personal API Keys
# export LINEAR_API_KEY=""

# ── Slack MCP (workspace messaging) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your token: api.slack.com → Your Apps → OAuth & Permissions → Bot Token
# export SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=""

# ── Firebase / Google Cloud ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by MCP servers that need a GCP project context
# export GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT="your-gcp-project-id"

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Adding a new MCP server?
#   1. Add its export line here (uncommented, with your real value)
#   2. Add its mcpServers block to .claude/settings.dev.json using ${VAR}
#   3. Add mcp__servername__* to permissions.allow in the same file
#   4. Re-source this file and restart Claude Code
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
